data.description: THE SELLER IS OFFERING THE BUYER $5,000 TOWARDS CLOSING COSTS FOR A FULL PRICE OFFER.  If you are looking for your new home within a 25 minute drive to a number of beautiful beaches, look no further.  This beautifully maintained 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom home in North Port has a number of great updates.  The home got a brand new roof and gutters after Hurricane Ian, even though this home stood up to the storm with no water penetration. The AC was replaced in 2021.The lanai has a beautiful new shiplap ceiling and is the perfect place to hang out and enjoy the Florida sunshine.  When you enter the home, you will experience a high ceiling and open floor plan with lots of great space for entertaining guests.  The home has a split floor plan that has a master bedroom with a large walk in closet and bathroom on one side of the home and the guest bedroom and guest bathroom on the other side of the home.  All of the interior doors are new and the home has new hurricane impact windows and sliders along with an existing hurricane impact garage door.  Both bathrooms in this home have been updated and new lighting fixtures and fans really make this home look great.  If you don't want the hassle of furnishing a home, you are in luck.  This house can be sold furnished.  There is nothing left for you to do but bring your beach chairs and relax.  Book your showing today!
